{"lemma":"جَدَّ","slug":"جَدَّ","root":"ج.د.د","root_slug":"ج-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جَدّ","root":"جدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5161","n5162","n5163"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be new"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be serious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be earnest"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَدَّ (jadda, “to be serious, to be earnest”)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seriousness, earnestness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"diligence, assiduity, eagerness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"good luck, good fortune"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandfather"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ancestor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"glory"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Majesty"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandeur"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"excellence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ancient"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew גד (gad)."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒadd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5161","headword_ar":"جَدٌّ","root":"jd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZ~N","text_ar":"حَظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, L, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baxotN","text_ar":"بَخْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the world,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in wordly circumstances;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advance in the world,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in worldly circumstances:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juduwdN","text_ar":"جُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajodaAdN","text_ar":"اَجْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajud~N","text_ar":"اَجُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN *uw jad~K fiY ka*aA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ ذُو جَدٍّ فِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is possessed of good fortune in such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And it is said in a trad. respecting the day of resurrection,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_i*aA A^aSoHaAbu Aljad~i maHobuwsuwna","text_ar":"وَاـِذَا اَصْحَابُ الجَدِّ مَحْبُوسُونَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And lo, the people who were possessed of good fortune and riches in the world were imprisoned."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And in a prayer, (L,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yanofaEu *aA Aljad~i minoka Aljad~u","text_ar":"لَا يَنْفَعُ ذَا الجَدِّ مِنْكَ الجَدُّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The good worldly fortune of him who is possessed of such fortune will not profit him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L,) in the world to come, (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in lieu of Thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L; *) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of obedience to Thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, and Mughnee in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in lieu of the good fortune that cometh from Thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not defend him from Thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mughnee ubi suprà. [See also another explanation below.]) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajad~aka laA tafoEalo","text_ar":"اَجَدَّكَ لَا تَفْعَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajad~ika","text_ar":"اَجَدِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajad~ika","text_ar":"وَجَدِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  One's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lot in life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means of subsistence that one receives from the bounty of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lifulaAnK fiY","text_ar":"لِفُلَانٍ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlA^amori jad~N","text_ar":"هٰذَا الاَمْرِ جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has in this thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of affairs, means of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Richness; competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of being in no need,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of having no wants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of having few wants."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA ynfE *A","text_ar":"لا ينفع ذا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljd~ mnk Aljd~","text_ar":"الجدّ منك الجدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [explained above, is said to mean]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Riches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not profit the possessor thereof with Thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for nothing will profit him but acting in obedience to Thee:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnk","text_ar":"منك"},{"kind":"text","text":"here signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einodaka","text_ar":"عِنْدَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Greatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"majesty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mujáhid, S, Mgh, Msb, K;) accord. to some, specially of God: (TA:) so in the Kur lxxii. 3: (S, TA:) or his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freedom from all wants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaAlaY jad~uka","text_ar":"تَعَالَى جَدُّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, TA,) in a trad. respecting prayer, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Exalted be thy greatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"majesty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, * TA.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajad~aka","text_ar":"اَجَدَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an interrogative phrase, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also, (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majoduwdN","text_ar":"مَجْدُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiydN","text_ar":"جَدِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~iy~N","text_ar":"جَدِّيٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~N","text_ar":"جُدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~iy~N","text_ar":"جُدِّيٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the last two with damm, (K,) applied to a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fortunate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed of good fortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed of good worldly fortune:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing great fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great good fortune:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [the words here given from the S are there coupled with synonyms of the same form, thus; ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiydN","text_ar":"جَدِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZiyZN","text_ar":"حَظِيظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoZuwZN","text_ar":"مَحْظُوظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majoduwdq","text_ar":"مَجْدُودق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N HaZ~u","text_ar":"جَدٌّ حَظُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZ~iY~N","text_ar":"حَظِّىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~iy~N","text_ar":"جَدِّيٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; on the authority of ISk:] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~N","text_ar":"جُدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, as an epithet applied to a man, is said by Sb to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majoduwdN","text_ar":"مَجْدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~Nwna","text_ar":"جُدٌّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only. (L.)       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~u","text_ar":"جَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A grandfather;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"father's father,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mother's father:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a higher ascendant; an ancestor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~apN","text_ar":"جَدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a grandmother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"father's mother,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mother's mother:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a female ancestor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl. of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajodaAdN","text_ar":"اَجْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juduwdN","text_ar":"جُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juduwdapN","text_ar":"جُدُودَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and of the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~aAtN","text_ar":"جَدَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajad~ika laA tafoEalo","text_ar":"وَجَدِّكَ لَا تَفْعَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~apN","text_ar":"جُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiydN","text_ar":"جَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","L","K","TA","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n5162","headword_ar":"جُدٌّ","root":"jd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~apN","text_ar":"جُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnib","text_ar":"جَانِب"},{"kind":"text","text":") of anything. (K.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well in a place where is much herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well abounding with water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) [and] so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"judojudN","text_ar":"جُدْجُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (KL;) but A'Obeyd says that this is not known: (L:) and, contr.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well containing little water: a scanty water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water little in quantity: a water at the extremity of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desert such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaAp","text_ar":"فَلَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old well:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL:) pl. (in all these senses, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajodaAdN","text_ar":"اَجْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","L","Th","KL"]},{"entry_id":"n5163","headword_ar":"جِدٌّ","root":"jd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to some an inf. n., but accord. to others a simple subst., (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a","text_ar":"جَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seriousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earnestness, contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hazolN","text_ar":"هَزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) in speech. (Msb.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvN jid~uhun~a jid~N wahazoluhun~a","text_ar":"ثَلَاثٌ جِدُّهُنَّ جِدٌّ وَهَزْلُهُنَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[There are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three things in relation to which what is serious is serious and what is jesting is serious"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a saying of Mohammad, whereby he forbade a man's divorcing and emancipating and marrying and then retracting, saying “ I was jesting; ” as was customary in the time of paganism. (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajid~aka","text_ar":"اَجِدَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajad~aka","text_ar":"اَجَدَّكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same; (S;) but the former is the more chaste; (TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~","text_ar":"جِدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~","text_ar":"جَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being thus used only as prefixed nouns: (S, K:) As says that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abijid~K minoka h`*aA","text_ar":"اَبِجِدٍّ مِنْكَ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Does this proceed from thee in seriousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in earnest?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~","text_ar":"جِدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the accus. case because of the rejection of the [prep.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":": AA says that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA laka A^ajid~FA minoka","text_ar":"مَا لَكَ اَجِدًّا مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What aileth thee? Doth it proceed from thee in seriousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in earnest?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jd~","text_ar":"جدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the accus. case as an inf. n.: Th says that the phrase as it occurs in poetry is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajid~aka","text_ar":"اَجِدَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr: (S:) but when it occurs with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a particle denoting an oath,] it is"},{"kind":"page_break","n":386},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajad~ika","text_ar":"وَجَدِّكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajad~ika","text_ar":"اَجَدِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], with fet-h: (S, K:) yon say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajad~ika laA tafoEalo","text_ar":"وَجَدِّكَ لَا تَفْعَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajad~aka","text_ar":"وَجَدَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By thy grandfather, do not"},{"kind":"text","text":"[such a thing]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune, do not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also, when you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajid~aka laA tafoEalo","text_ar":"اَجِدَّكَ لَا تَفْعَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajid~ika","text_ar":"اَجِدِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.) is substituted for a particle of swearing, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^all~`hi laA^afoEalan~a","text_ar":"اَللّٰهِ لَاَفْعَلَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] the meaning is, I adjure thee"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy truth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy seriousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earnestness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"do not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and when you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tafoEalo","text_ar":"لَا تَفْعَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajad~aka","text_ar":"اَجَدَّكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajad~ika","text_ar":"اَجَدِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] the meaning is, I adjure thee"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by thy fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune, do not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K:) Aboo- 'Alee Esh-Shalowbeenee asserts that it implies the signification of an oath. (MF.) In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~k lA tafoEalu","text_ar":"اجدّك لا تَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", AAF says, we may consider"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA tfEl","text_ar":"لا تفعل"},{"kind":"text","text":"as put in the place of a denotative of state; or the phrase may be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~k A^ano laA tafoEala","text_ar":"اجدّك اَنْ لَا تَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"An","text_ar":"ان"},{"kind":"text","text":"being suppressed, and its government annulled: [therefore it may be rendered, in the former case,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is it with seriousness on thy part, thou doing"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing? and in the latter case,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is it with seriousness on thy part"},{"kind":"text","text":"that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou will not do"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing? i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dost thou mean seriously"},{"kind":"text","text":"that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou will not do"},{"kind":"text","text":"it? or in this case,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~k","text_ar":"اجدّك"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be used as a form of adjuration in one of the senses explained above, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tafoEalu","text_ar":"لَا تَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may mean, that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou do not"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~k","text_ar":"اجدّك"},{"kind":"text","text":"may mean"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajad~aka","text_ar":"وَجَدَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (explained above, and so in the three exs. below,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tafoEalu","text_ar":"لَا تَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou wilt not do"},{"kind":"text","text":"it:] and, as AHei says, there is here a nice point, which is this; that the noun [meaning the pronoun] to which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jd~","text_ar":"جدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is prefixed should agree in person with the verb which follows it; so that one should say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~iY laA A^ukorimuka","text_ar":"اجدِّى لَا اُكْرِمُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~ka laA tafoEalu","text_ar":"اجدّكَ لَا تَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajd~hu laA yazuwrunaA","text_ar":"اجدّهُ لَا يَزُورُنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jd~","text_ar":"جدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. corroborating the proposition that follows it. (MF.) ―         -b2-  Also, [and in this case, likewise, accord. to some an inf. n., but accord. to others a simple subst., (see, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a","text_ar":"جَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A striving, labour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"toil; exertion of one's self,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one's power"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"efforts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endeavours"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability; vigorousness, strenuousness, laboriousness, diligence, studiousness, sedulousness, earnestness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"energy; painstaking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extraordinary painstaking;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K;) in affairs, (S,) or in an affair. (Msb, K.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~FA","text_ar":"جِدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In a great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an extraordinary, degree; greatly, much, exceedingly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extraordinarily; very; very greatly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very much; extremely"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as in the phrase, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN muHosinN jid~FA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مُحْسِنٌ جِدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is beneficent in a great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an extraordinary, degree; very, exceedingly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremely, beneficent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: you should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~FA","text_ar":"جَدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb. * [In my copy of the Msb, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHsn jd~A bAlftH","text_ar":"محسن جدّا بالفتح"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the context shows that there is an omission here, and that, after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jd~A","text_ar":"جدّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", we should read, as in the S,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA taqulo jad~FA","text_ar":"وَلَا تَقُلْ جَدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~FA","text_ar":"جِدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in a phrase of this kind] is put in the accus. case as an inf. n. [of which the verb is understood; so that, in the ex. given above, the proper meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yajid~u fiY","text_ar":"يَجِدُّ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iHosaAni jid~FA","text_ar":"الاـِحْسَانِ جِدًّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"striving in beneficence with a great striving"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because it is not from the same root as the preceding word, nor is it identical with it [in meaning]. (L.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY h`*aA xaTarN","text_ar":"فِى هٰذَا خَطَرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~a EaZiymK","text_ar":"جِدَّ عَظِيمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZiymN jid~FA","text_ar":"عَظِيمٌ جِدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In this is a very,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an extremely, great danger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"risk"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*A AlEaAlimu jid~a AlEaAlimi","text_ar":"هٰذا العَالِمُ جِدَّ العَالِمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the learned"},{"kind":"text","text":"man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the extremely"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the very"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"learned"},{"kind":"text","text":"man. (L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA EaAlimN jid~a EaAlimK","text_ar":"هٰذَا عَالِمٌ جِدَّ عَالِمٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a learned"},{"kind":"text","text":"man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an extremely"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a very"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"learned"},{"kind":"text","text":"man. (L, * K.) ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Haste."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K, TA.) So in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN EalaY jid~i A^amorK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ عَلَى جِدِّ اَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is in haste in an affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Executed seriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in earnest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which there is no jesting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and excessive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaq~aqN mubaAlagN fiyhi","text_ar":"مُحَقَّقٌ مُبَالَغٌ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaq~aqN fiyhi wamubaAlagN fiyhi","text_ar":"مُحَقَّقٌ فِيهِ وَمُبَالَغٌ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~a fiY A^amorihi","text_ar":"جَدَّ فِى اَمْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jid~N","text_ar":"جِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus used as an epithet having an intensive signification because it is originally an inf. n., or as some say, a simple subst.]: (L, K:) applied in this sense to a punishment: (L:) and also applied to a pace. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nS","text_ar":"نص"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~apN","text_ar":"جُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jadiydN","text_ar":"جَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA","Lth","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}